            <title>[AVRO-862] Responder.respond return nothing  when schema.AvroException </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-862</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;location: &lt;b&gt;avro\ip.py:339&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;    except schema.AvroException, e:&lt;br/&gt;
      error = AvroRemoteException(str(e))&lt;br/&gt;
      buffer_encoder = io.BinaryEncoder(StringIO())&lt;br/&gt;
      META_WRITER.write(response_metadata, buffer_encoder)&lt;br/&gt;
      buffer_encoder.write_boolean(True)&lt;br/&gt;
      self.write_error(SYSTEM_ERROR_SCHEMA, error, buffer_encoder)&lt;br/&gt;
    return buffer_writer.getvalue()&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if schema.AvroException occur, buffer_encoder recreate with new StringIO, and nothing return in buffer_writer&lt;/p&gt;</description>
