<item>
            <title>[AVRO-865] Upgrade to Jansson 2.1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-865</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There have been a couple of releases on the Jansson JSON library that we&apos;re using in the C bindings.  There are a couple of new features that will be especially helpful to us:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Jansson now supports 64-bit integer values, so Avro &lt;tt&gt;long&lt;/tt&gt; values will encode correctly&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Jansson can now encode JSON values that aren&apos;t top-level arrays or objects, so we won&apos;t need a special workaround for encoding Avro scalars&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
